data.description: Only a job transfer brings this home back on the market. Beautiful 2 story 4 bedroom 2 and a half bath colonial with a bright and cheerful open concept. Upon entering this naturally lit home through the new front door, you will enjoy the open concept of the living room and dining room on the two sides of the entrance hall. A wonderful combination of hardwood and composite flooring throughout the house will grasp your attention and bring the warmth and balance to each room. Walk past the entrance way and enter the vaulted ceiling Family Room with gas fireplace book ended by bright windows overlooking the canal views. Off to one side of the Family room is a first floor office/den, remodeled half bath and on the opposite side is the Kitchen and stairs to the second floor. Once entering the Kitchen you will be greeted by maple cabinetry, granite counters and center island work space. The eat-in country style kitchen offers a new slider that provides access to the new deck with views of the canal and  stairs to the partially fenced rear yard. Venturing upstairs there is a owners suite with four piece bath and walk-in closet. Three additional large bedrooms along the open hallway that overlooks the family room really makes for a warm and friendly home all together. Lets not forget to visit the basement which has a walkout door to the rear yard. The basement does have the plumbing in place for a bathroom installation and ready the new owner to finish. Bring you buyers to this magnificent home!   ***Showings Start 11/26 at Open House 12-3***
